I still get sad sometimes for not having that daddy-daugther bond, someone who loves you and protects you unconditionally. It's so sad not being able to relate to this stories and not having a male role model in my life, I kinda have had to imagine that standard and raise myself. But I'm happy that people do have that bond, it makes me realize that good dads exist. So sad that the first man in my life didn't really loved me.

snippet.textDisplay:
Lovely song....truly understand the meaning of this...my dad did the same....i was 2 1/2 years old when they crossed me over....i don't remember much but have heard the stories...my dad worked hard for us to get resident cards...crazy how those cards, people called green cards but in reality they were never green! When I would tell co workers I was born in Mexico, they literally would get in shock because I never dressed or spoke a certain way...like how am I suppose to dress and talk? I would jokingly say, maybe I need to wear a fancy dress to a grocery store so people could see that I wasn't born here?! Hehehe....well time flies...became a US citizen at 18 years old after graduating from High school.....only had speeding tickets as my crime...i thought i was fast and the furious girl in my brand new car my dad purchased for me two weeks before my 16th birthday....i became a Medical Coder working from home, built our custom home in 2018, own my brand new car that hubby and I got stinking brand new off the lot in 2014....have two beautiful young daughters, 16 and 10, with a brand new baby boy 8 months old...been with hubby since 2002 and been married since 2005....life's been good and through our tough times, God has lifted us up. I lost my dad to a second stroke in Feb 2014, so he never got to see us raise livestock, built our home from ground up, meet baby grandson....i didn't get along with my parents but i loved him and love my mom...this song made me tear up....

I only hear Camila's songs when daughters listen to it, and I like her...she doesn't look trashy, I haven't heard a song of hers that sounds trashy speaking of her body or seducing men, etc or seeing her in hoe-ish clothes that reveals everything. Very nice song dedicated to her dad....
